## Amplitude Analytics API Suite

Amplitude provides a comprehensive suite of REST APIs for analytics data ingestion, user management, data export, and privacy compliance. The platform serves as a complete analytics solution with real-time event tracking, user behavior analysis, and enterprise-grade data management capabilities.

## Product Relationships and Architecture

The API ecosystem is organized around several core functional areas:

**Data Ingestion Layer:**
- **HTTP V2 API** serves as the primary event ingestion endpoint (`api2.amplitude.com/2/httpapi`)
- **Batch Event Upload API** handles bulk data uploads with 20MB payload limits
- **Identify API** manages user property updates and device-to-user ID mappings
- **Group Identify API** supports group-level analytics through the Accounts add-on
- **Attribution API** processes mobile advertising attribution events

**Data Access and Export:**
- **Export API** provides bulk event data extraction in zipped JSON format
- **Dashboard REST API** offers programmatic access to analytics visualizations and metrics
- **User Profile API** retrieves comprehensive user profiles including properties, cohorts, and predictions

**User and Privacy Management:**
- **User Privacy API** handles GDPR/CCPA compliance through programmatic data deletion
- **CCPA DSAR API** provides Data Subject Access Request functionality
- **User Mapping API** enables cross-project user aliasing via the Portfolio add-on

**Configuration and Metadata:**
- **Taxonomy API** manages event schema, properties, and data classifications for Enterprise users
- **Lookup Table APIs** (v1 deprecated, v2 current) augment events with CSV-based property mappings
- **SCIM API** handles user provisioning and group management for enterprise identity providers

**Analytics and Monitoring:**
- **Behavioral Cohorts API** manages user segments with asynchronous download workflows
- **Chart Annotations API** enables programmatic chart annotation management
- **Releases API** tracks product releases and deployment workflows
- **Event Streaming Metrics API** monitors delivery metrics for event streams

## Key Nomenclature and Definitions

**Core Identifiers:**
- `amplitude_id`: Amplitude's internal user identifier
- `user_id`: Customer-defined user identifier
- `device_id`: Device-specific identifier
- `session_id`: Session tracking identifier
- `insert_id`: Deduplication identifier for events

**Event Structure:**
- `event_type`: The name/category of the tracked event
- `event_properties`: Custom properties associated with specific events
- `user_properties`: Properties associated with users across sessions
- `group_properties`: Properties for group-level analytics (Accounts add-on)

**Property Operations:**
- `$set`: Set property value
- `$setOnce`: Set property only if not already set
- `$add`: Add numeric value to existing property
- `$append`/`$prepend`: Add values to array properties
- `$unset`: Remove property
- `$remove`: Remove specific values from arrays

**API Patterns:**
- **Asynchronous workflows**: Three-step process (request → poll status → download) used in Cohorts, DSAR, and Export APIs
- **Rate limiting**: Implemented across APIs with specific limits (e.g., 1000 events/second, 500 requests/month)
- **HTTP Basic Authentication**: Standard authentication method using API keys and secrets
- **Cost-based limiting**: Enterprise APIs use cost-per-query models with concurrent and period limits

## Broader Product Ecosystem Integration

The APIs integrate with several Amplitude product tiers and add-ons:

**Plan Dependencies:**
- **Growth/Enterprise plans**: Required for advanced APIs like Cohorts (500 requests/month limit)
- **Activation plan**: Required for User Profile API access
- **Accounts add-on**: Enables group-level analytics and Group Identify functionality
- **Portfolio add-on**: Enables cross-project user mapping capabilities

**Regional Infrastructure:**
- Standard endpoints: `api2.amplitude.com`, `data-api.amplitude.com`
- EU residency: `api.eu.amplitude.com` for GDPR compliance
- Profile API: `profile-api.amplitude.com` (EU region unavailable)

**Integration Patterns:**
- **Identity Provider Integration**: SCIM API supports Okta, JumpCloud, and other enterprise IdPs
- **Warehouse Integration**: Change Data Capture (CDC) for data warehouse synchronization
- **Streaming Destinations**: Event streaming with delivery metrics monitoring
- **Amazon S3 Integration**: Pre-signed URLs for large file downloads and exports

## Key API Endpoints and Invocations

**Primary Ingestion:**
```
POST api2.amplitude.com/2/httpapi
POST api2.amplitude.com/identify
POST api2.amplitude.com/groupidentify
POST api2.amplitude.com/attribution
```

**Data Export:**
```
GET api2.amplitude.com/api/2/export
GET profile-api.amplitude.com/v1/userprofile
```

**Management Operations:**
```
POST api2.amplitude.com/api/2/deletions/users
GET/POST api/3/cohorts (Behavioral Cohorts)
POST data-api.amplitude.com/api/3/lookup_table
```

**Enterprise Features:**
```
GET/POST/PUT/DELETE taxonomy endpoints (Enterprise)
POST/GET/PATCH core.amplitude.com/scim/1/ (SCIM)
```

The platform enforces comprehensive rate limiting (ranging from 1 request/second to 1000 events/second), payload size limits (1MB-20MB depending on plan), and provides detailed error handling with HTTP status codes for throttling (429), payload limits (413), and validation errors.